Ease to Next Key, ease the key value to the next key. <SHIFT> ease to the previous key.
Flatten to Average Value, <SHIFT> weld all selected keys to average value and time.
Flatten, <SHIFT> flatten to the last selected key.
Grow Key Selection, <SHIFT> shrink key selection.
Loop, copies the first key value to the last frame of the current animation range. <SHIFT> copy the first key value of the current animation to the last one.
Mirror Tangents, mirrors the tangents of the selected key to the adjacent ones.
Relax keys, ease key values and tangents between the first and last keys of the selection. <SHIFT> align the keys between the first and last keys of the selection.
Scale Tangents Down, <SHIFT> scale the inner tangent handles of the selection.
Scale Tangents Up, <SHIFT> scale the inner tangent handles of the selection.
Select Next Key, moves the key selection forward. <SHIFT> move the key selection backwards.
Snap Scale, works with Scale Values tool. Moves the scale origin to the first selected key.
Space Keys Evenly, spaces the key selection evenly in time between the first and last keys. <SHIFT> space evenly in value.
Split, deletes the selected key and creates two new keys.
